// Two chained pyth-nested checks to a single far join (20). check1 (nodes 0/1/2) falls
// through to check2 (node 4); both checks' fail-arms jump to join 20.
//
//   check1: 0 cond(a>b) {1 cond(thr){3 fail->20 | 4=next}} {2 cond(thr){5 fail->20 | 4=next}}
//   check2: 4 cond(a>b) {6 cond(thr){8 fail->20 | 10=rest}} {7 cond(thr){9 fail->20 | 10=rest}}
//   10 rest -> 20
//   20 join sink
//
// 4.idom = 0, 20.idom = 0. When node 0 hoists orphans [4, 20], check2's structure (4_body)
// sits as a sibling BEFORE the join 20. The fail-jumps `goto 20` inside check1's arms are at
// tail positions (reachable by elide_tail_jump_to), but check2's fail-jumps are buried inside
// 4_body's non-last IfElse — elide_tail_jump_to only walks the Seq's LAST item, so they survive.
cond,0,1,2
cond,1,3,4
cond,2,5,4
code,3,20
code,5,20
cond,4,6,7
cond,6,8,10
cond,7,9,10
code,8,20
code,9,20
code,10,20
code,20
